Lekin yaad rakhiye, package.json mein dependency version ko sahi karna hi sabse achha tareeka hai long-term ke liye. Render par build command modify karna sirf temporary workaround ho sakta hai.

Agar aap mujhe bata sakte hain ki aapne apne local package.json ko update kiya hai ya nahi, toh main uske according aur specific help de paunga.

Ky build command me ek sath bhot codes daal skte h?


Haan, Render ke build command field mein aap ek saath multiple commands daal sakte hain. Aapko bas un commands ko && operator se separate karna hoga.

Example:

Agar aap pehle kuch aur karna chahte hain aur phir npm install run karna chahte hain, toh aap aisa kar sakte hain:

Bash

echo "Starting build process..." && npm install && echo "Dependencies installed."
Is example mein:

echo "Starting build process...": Yeh ek message log mein print karega.
&&: Yeh operator pehle command ke successfully complete hone ke baad hi agle command ko run karta hai.
npm install: Yeh aapke dependencies install karega.
&&: Phir se, yeh operator npm install ke successfully complete hone ke baad hi agle command ko run karega.
echo "Dependencies installed.": Yeh ek aur message log mein print karega agar npm install successfully ho jaata hai.
Aap apne dependency conflict ko solve karne ke liye bhi multiple commands use kar sakte hain, jaise maine pehle suggest kiya tha:

Bash

npm install cloudinary@1.41.0 && npm install
Is command mein, yeh pehle cloudinary ka specific version install karne ki koshish karega, aur agar woh successful hota hai toh phir npm install (jo aapke package.json mein listed baaki dependencies ko install karega) run karega.

Lekin dhyan rahe: Agar pehla command fail ho jaata hai (jaise cloudinary@1.41.0 nahi milta hai), toh && ki wajah se doosra command (npm install) run nahi hoga.

Ek aur tareeka (thoda zyada robust):

Agar aap chahte hain ki npm install hamesha run ho, chahe pehla command fail ho ya na ho, toh aap ; (semicolon) use kar sakte hain:

Bash

npm install cloudinary@1.41.0 ; npm install
Lekin && zyada common hai build processes mein kyunki aap generally chahte hain ki agar koi step fail ho jaaye toh build aage na badhe.

Summary:

Haan, aap && use karke ek saath multiple commands Render ke build command field mein daal sakte hain. Iska istemaal aap dependency issues ko try karne aur resolve karne ke liye kar sakte hain. Yaad rahe ki commands usi order mein run honge jis order mein aap unhe likhenge.

