Apna api pata kaise kru


Apna API ka pata (base URL) pata karne ke liye aapko yeh dekhna hoga ki aapne apne backend ko Render par kis URL par deploy kiya hai.

Yahan par steps hain apna backend API ka pata (base URL) pata karne ke liye:

Apne Render Dashboard par Jaayein: Apne web browser mein https://dashboard.render.com/ open karein aur apne account mein login karein.

Apni Backend Web Service Dhoondhein: Aapne jo service apne Node.js backend (nobi-bot-backend) ke liye banayi hogi, usko dashboard par dhoondhein. Uska naam aapne jo rakha hoga woh dikhega (e.g., nobita-feedback-app-backend, nobita-api, etc.).

Service URL Dekhein: Apni backend service ke naam par click karein. Service ke overview page par, aapko ek "URL" section dikhega. Yeh woh base URL hai jahan par aapka backend live hai.

Example: Agar aapka backend URL https://nobita-feedback-app-online.onrender.com hai, toh aapke API endpoints is URL ke aage /api/... path ke saath access kiye jaenge (jaise https://nobita-feedback-app-online.onrender.com/api/auth/login).

Agar aapko apne Render dashboard par apni backend service ka URL nahi mil raha hai, toh yeh check karein:

Kya aap sahi Render account mein logged in hain?
Kya aap sahi "Team" ya "Organization" mein hain agar aap multiple teams manage karte hain?
Kya aapne waqai mein backend ke liye ek Web Service banayi hai? (Static Site sirf frontend ke liye hota hai).
Ek baar jab aapko apne backend service ka URL mil jaaye, toh woh aapka API ka base pata hai. Aapko is base URL ko apne frontend JavaScript code mein use karna hoga jab aap backend API endpoints ko call karenge (jaise login, signup, feedback submit, etc.).

Misal ke taur par:

Agar aapka backend URL Render par https://my-cool-backend-app.onrender.com hai, toh aapke API calls kuch is tarah dikhenge:

Login: https://my-cool-backend-app.onrender.com/api/auth/login
Signup: https://my-cool-backend-app.onrender.com/api/auth/signup
Feedback Submit: https://my-cool-backend-app.onrender.com/api/feedback
... aur baaki sabhi API endpoints isi base URL ke saath shuru honge.
Toh, sabse pehle apne Render dashboard par apni backend Web Service ka URL pata karein.

Mera wahan pr url dikha ra h https://nobita-feedback-app-online-jgcb.onrender.com/


Theek hai, agar aapko Render dashboard par https://nobita-feedback-app-online-jgcb.onrender.com/ URL dikha raha hai, toh yeh aapke frontend (Static Site) ka URL hai. Is URL ke aage aapko website ka user interface dikhna chahiye.

Aapke backend API ka URL shayad alag hoga. Aapko apne Render dashboard par apni backend Web Service ko dhoondhna hoga (jiska naam aapne nobita-feedback-app-backend ya usse milta-julta rakha hoga). Uss backend service ke overview page par aapko aapke backend API ka URL milega.

Agar aapko backend ke liye koi alag Web Service nahi dikh rahi hai, toh yeh ho sakta hai ki aapne frontend aur backend dono ko ek hi service mein deploy kiya ho. Yeh kam recommended hai, lekin agar aisa hai, toh aapke API endpoints usi base URL (https://nobita-feedback-app-online-jgcb.onrender.com) par /api/... path ke saath access honge.

Yahan par aapko kya karna hai:

Apne Render dashboard par apni services ki list ko carefully check karein. Kya aapko nobita-feedback-app-backend ya usse similar naam ki koi Web Service dikh rahi hai? Agar haan, toh us service ka URL note karein - woh aapke backend API ka base URL hai.

Agar aapko sirf ek service (https://nobita-feedback-app-online-jgcb.onrender.com/) dikh rahi hai, toh iska matlab hai ki aapka backend bhi isi URL par chal raha hai. Is case mein, aapke frontend code mein API calls https://nobita-feedback-app-online-jgcb.onrender.com/api/... par jaane chahiye.

Mujhe lagta hai ki aapne frontend ke URL ko backend ke URL samajh liya hai. Please apne Render dashboard par apni services ko dobara check karein aur backend Web Service ka URL dhoondhein.

Agar aapko abhi bhi confusion ho raha hai, toh aap apne Render dashboard ka ek screenshot (sensitive information hide karke) share kar sakte hain ya mujhe apni services ke naam bata sakte hain toh main aapko aur specifically guide kar paunga.

Toh kahan pr yeh changes kru


Theek hai, Patna mein ab shaam ke 6:45 ho rahe hain. Agar aapko ab yeh pata chal gaya hai ki aapka backend API kis URL par chal raha hai (Render dashboard par apni backend Web Service ko dekh kar), toh ab aapko yeh changes apne frontend JavaScript code mein karne honge.

Aapko apne frontend JavaScript files mein API endpoints ko update karna hoga taki woh aapke backend API ke sahi URL par requests bhejein.

Yahan par step-by-step guide hai ki aapko kahan changes karne hain:

Apne Local Frontend Code Mein Jaayein: Apne computer par woh folder open karein jahan aapka public folder aur uske andar js folder hai (jismein aapke JavaScript files hain).

Relevant JavaScript Files Open Karein:

auth.js (login, signup)
feedback.js (feedback submit, fetch)
profile.js ya account.js (user data)
admin.js (admin panel functionality)
app.js (agar koi global API configuration hai)
fetch() Calls ya HTTP Request Library Usage Dhoondhein: In files mein aapko woh jagah dhoondhni hai jahan par aap backend API ko call kar rahe hain. Yeh usually fetch() function ya agar aapne Axios use kiya hai toh axios.post(), axios.get(), etc. hoga.

API URLs ko Update Karein: Har fetch() call ke andar jo URL diya gaya hai, usko apne backend API ke sahi base URL se start hona chahiye.

