Theek hai, main aapki madad karunga aapke JavaScript code mein API calls dhoondhne mein. Main aapko specific code nahi de sakta kyunki mere paas aapke files ka access nahi hai, lekin main aapko bataunga ki aap apne code mein kahan aur kaise dhoondh sakte hain.

Aapko apne frontend JavaScript files mein API calls dhoondhne honge. In files mein aapko fetch() function ya agar aapne Axios library use ki hai toh axios.get(), axios.post(), etc. ka istemaal dikhega.

Yahan par woh files hain jinhe aapko check karna chahiye:

public/js/auth.js: Login aur signup se related API calls (e.g., /api/auth/login, /api/auth/signup).
public/js/feedback.js: Feedback submit karne aur fetch karne se related API calls (e.g., /api/feedback, /api/feedback/me).
public/js/profile.js ya public/js/account.js: User profile data fetch karne ya update karne se related API calls (e.g., /api/users/me, /api/account).
public/js/admin.js: Admin panel se users aur feedback fetch karne aur delete karne se related API calls (e.g., /api/admin/users, /api/admin/feedbacks, /api/admin/users/:id, /api/admin/feedbacks/:id).
public/js/app.js: Yahan par global API URL configuration ya kuch initial data fetching ho sakti hai.
Code mein API calls kaise dhoondhein:

Apne code editor mein in files ko open karein.
fetch( ya axios. search karein. Aap apne code editor ka search functionality (Ctrl+F ya Cmd+F) use kar sakte hain.
Har fetch() ya axios. call ko carefully check karein.
Dekhein ki URL kahan se aa raha hai (hardcoded string hai ya kisi variable se).
Ensure karein ki URL sahi format mein hai aur aapke backend API ke base URL se start ho raha hai (e.g., https://nobita-feedback-app-online.onrender.com/api/... ya agar aapka frontend aur backend ek hi URL par hain toh /api/...).
Check karein ki kya aap sahi HTTP method use kar rahe hain (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE).
Dekhein ki kya aap sahi headers bhej rahe hain (especially Content-Type: application/json agar aap JSON data bhej rahe hain).
Example:

JavaScript

// auth.js mein
