Tum dhudh kr do


Mai aapke code files ko directly access nahi kar sakta. Mai ek AI hoon aur mere paas aapke local computer ya Render deployment se files dekhne ki permission nahi hai.

Lekin, mai aapko woh tareeke bata sakta hoon jinka istemaal karke aap khud apne code mein API calls dhoondh sakte hain:

Apne Code Editor ka "Find in Files" Feature Use Karein:

Aapke code editor (jaise VS Code, Sublime Text, Atom) mein "Find in Files" ya "Search Across Project" naam ka ek feature hota hai (usually Ctrl+Shift+F ya Cmd+Shift+F press karne par aata hai).
Is feature mein aap woh strings search kar sakte hain jo API calls mein commonly use hote hain, jaise:
fetch(
axios.
'api/'
"api/"
Aapka backend URL (e.g., 'https://nobita-feedback-app-online.onrender.com')
Editor aapke poore project mein woh lines highlight kar dega jahan yeh strings milenge. Phir aap un lines ko check kar sakte hain ki kya woh API calls hain aur kya URLs sahi hain.

Apne JavaScript Files ko Step-by-Step Read Karein:

Apne public/js/ folder mein files ko ek-ek karke open karein (auth.js, feedback.js, etc.).
Code ko padhte jaayein aur dekhein ki kahan par aap fetch() ya axios. ka istemaal kar rahe hain.
Har API call ke URL ko verify karein.
Aapko kya check karna hai jab aap API calls dhoondhein:

Base URL: Kya API URL aapke backend Render URL se start ho raha hai? (e.g., https://nobita-feedback-app-online.onrender.com) ya agar frontend/backend ek hi jagah hain toh /api se?
Endpoint: Kya base URL ke baad sahi API endpoint diya gaya hai? (e.g., /api/auth/login, /api/feedback). Spelling aur case ka dhyaan rakhein.
HTTP Method: Kya aap sahi method (POST login/signup/submit ke liye, GET data fetch karne ke liye) use kar rahe hain?
Headers: Kya aap Content-Type: application/json header bhej rahe hain jab aap JSON data bhej rahe hain?
Mai jaanta hoon ki aap chahte hain ki mai khud dhoondh doon, lekin technical limitations ki wajah se mai aisa nahi kar sakta. Aapko yeh process khud se karna hoga. Agar aapko kisi specific line of code mein shak hai, toh aap us line ko yahan share kar sakte hain, aur mai usko dekhkar bata paunga ki woh API call sahi lag rahi hai ya nahi.

Abhi aap apne code editor ka "Find in Files" feature use karein aur 'fetch(' search karein. Jo results milte hain unko ek-ek karke check karein aur dekhein ki URL sahi hai ya nahi.

Agar aapko pehla API call milta hai jismein aapko shak hai, toh us line ko yahan paste karein. Hum wahan se shuru kar sakte hain.





